item.title: Enable port
item.dc:creator: @dd1 dd
item.description:
@dd1 wrote:

Don’t you watch any TV?

BT has a plan - and that’s to get one of their Home Hubs into everyone’s house. The FrequencyCast podcast team thought we’d give you a guide as to what the BT Home Hub is all about, and why BT would like your home to have one.

Essentially, the BT Home Hub is intended to be the main connection point between BT’s phone network and BT Total Broadband service, and your home. The Hub is to the the central point for communication - home phone, mobile phone, wireless networking, broadband Internet and television services.
